# Trivy suppressions — each entry requires a documented justification.

# DS-0002: Dockerfile must specify a non-root USER
# Suppressed because the container intentionally starts as root to fix
# bind-mount ownership (chown /.archon appuser:appuser), then uses
# docker-entrypoint.sh + gosu to drop to appuser (UID 1001) before
# running the application. This is the standard Docker pattern for
# containers that need runtime volume permission setup. Adding a USER
# instruction would break the chown path for host bind mounts.
DS-0002

# GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq: uuid@11.1.0 (MEDIUM)
# Transitive dep of @mariozechner/pi-coding-agent. Fix requires uuid@14
# which is a major-version breaking change. Severity is MEDIUM; the
# community Pi provider is opt-in and not part of the default install.
GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq
